headline: Major waste companies spent more than $545M on M&A in Q3
summary: GFL and its subsidiaries acquired companies in Illinois, Oklahoma and Georgia, while Waste Connections focused on Florida-based deals and Republic bought haulers in Kentucky and Montana. WM and Casella focused on tuck-ins.
